SIMPLE: enginous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enginous
<hw>En"gi*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>engignos</ets>. See <er>Ingenious</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to an engine.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That one act gives, like an <qex>enginous</qex> wheel,⟦br⟧
Motion to all.</q> <rj><qau>Decker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Contrived with care; ingenious.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mark of all <qex>enginous</qex> drifts.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Engird</ent>⟦br⟧
